'''N-philes''' are group of [[radical (chemistry)|radical]] molecules which are specifically attracted to the [[Carbon–nitrogen bond|C=N bonds]], defying often the selectivity rules of [[electrophilic]] attack. N-philes can often masquerade as electrophiles, where [[acyl]] radicals are excellent examples which interact with [[Pi electrons]] of aryl groups.

